    • hydrateTPflash

      public void hydrateTPflash()
      Perform a TP flash with hydrate phase equilibrium calculation.

      This method calculates the equilibrium phases at given temperature and pressure, including the hydrate phase if conditions favor hydrate formation. The hydrate fraction and composition are calculated using the CPA EOS approach (Statoil/Equinor model).

      After calling this method, the system will contain the hydrate phase (if formed) with correct composition based on cavity occupancy calculations. The hydrate phase will appear in prettyPrint() output with the header "HYDRATE".

      Example usage: 

       SystemInterface fluid = new SystemSrkCPAstatoil(273.15, 50.0);
 fluid.addComponent("methane", 0.9);
 fluid.addComponent("water", 0.1);
 fluid.setMixingRule(10); // CPA mixing rule

 ThermodynamicOperations ops = new ThermodynamicOperations(fluid);
 ops.hydrateTPflash();

 fluid.prettyPrint(); // Shows GAS, AQUEOUS, HYDRATE columns
 double hydrateFraction = fluid.getHydrateFraction();
      See Also:
      • TPHydrateFlash

    • hydrateTPflash

      public void hydrateTPflash(boolean checkForSolids)
      Perform a TP flash with hydrate phase equilibrium calculation.

      This method calculates the equilibrium phases at given temperature and pressure, including the hydrate phase if conditions favor hydrate formation.

      Parameters:
      checkForSolids - Set true to also check for solid phases (ice, wax, etc.)
      See Also:
      • hydrateTPflash()

    • gasHydrateTPflash

      public void gasHydrateTPflash()
      Perform a TP flash targeting gas-hydrate equilibrium without aqueous phase.

      This method calculates equilibrium between gas and hydrate phases, attempting to eliminate the aqueous phase when water content is low enough. This is useful for modeling scenarios where trace water in gas is entirely consumed by hydrate formation.

      Example usage for gas-hydrate equilibrium: 

       SystemInterface fluid = new SystemSrkCPAstatoil(273.15 - 10.0, 200.0);
 fluid.addComponent("methane", 0.9999);
 fluid.addComponent("water", 0.0001); // 100 ppm water
 fluid.setMixingRule(10);

 ThermodynamicOperations ops = new ThermodynamicOperations(fluid);
 ops.gasHydrateTPflash(); // Targets gas-hydrate equilibrium

 fluid.prettyPrint(); // May show only GAS and HYDRATE phases
      See Also:
      • hydrateTPflash()

    • asphalteneOnsetPressure

      public double asphalteneOnsetPressure()
      Calculates the asphaltene onset pressure at the current system temperature.

      The onset pressure is where asphaltenes begin to precipitate from the oil phase. This typically occurs during pressure depletion near the bubble point.

      Example usage: 

       ThermodynamicOperations ops = new ThermodynamicOperations(fluid);
 double onsetP = ops.asphalteneOnsetPressure();
      Returns:
      onset pressure in bara, or NaN if no onset found
